uas7616MIBVersion.name: uas7616MIBVersion
uas7616MIBVersion.description: The version number of the MIB, to allow products to know which MIB is being supported. The version number will be x.yzT where x is a major revision (1-9), y is a minor revision(0-9), z is a typo revision (0-9) and T indicates the MIB is still a test revision(A-Z). When a release is complete no T should exist.

uas7616WhatAreYouTable.name: uas7616WhatAreYouTable
uas7616WhatAreYouTable.description: The GDC 7616 What Are You Table.

uas7616WhatAreYouEntry.name: uas7616WhatAreYouEntry
uas7616WhatAreYouEntry.description: An entry in the GDC 7616 What Are You table.

uas7616WhatAreYouIndex.name: uas7616WhatAreYouIndex
uas7616WhatAreYouIndex.description: This object is the identifier of the 7616 What Are You table.

uas7616CodeRev.name: uas7616CodeRev
uas7616CodeRev.description: This function returns the firmware code level. Example A- ,B-

uas7616AlarmStatus.name: uas7616AlarmStatus
uas7616AlarmStatus.description: The current alarms of the unit without the alarm masks.

uas7616SystemTimingGenStatus.name: uas7616SystemTimingGenStatus
uas7616SystemTimingGenStatus.description: Indicates if the units configured for primary or secondary system clock are actually supplying clock and if it is the 8hkz, 4mhz, or both.

uas7616ConfigIndex.name: uas7616ConfigIndex
uas7616ConfigIndex.description: A unique index for the Configuration Table.

uas7616TXClockSource.name: uas7616TXClockSource
uas7616TXClockSource.description: Object to select the Transmit Clock Source for the 7616.

uas7616TerminationType.name: uas7616TerminationType
uas7616TerminationType.description: Object to select the Termination Type for the 7616.

uas7616ChADataRate.name: uas7616ChADataRate
uas7616ChADataRate.description: Object to select the Data Rate on Channel A, Loop n.

uas7616ChBDataRate.name: uas7616ChBDataRate
uas7616ChBDataRate.description: Object to select the Data Rate on Channel B, Loop n.

uas7616ControlEntry.name: uas7616ControlEntry
uas7616ControlEntry.description: An entry in the GDC 7616 Control table.

uas7616ControlIndex.name: uas7616ControlIndex
uas7616ControlIndex.description: This object is the identifier of the 7616 Control table.

uas7616SoftReset.name: uas7616SoftReset
uas7616SoftReset.description: Forces a soft reset on the network element. The reset selection is write only. The normal selection is read only.

uas7616EraseConfig.name: uas7616EraseConfig
uas7616EraseConfig.description: Forces an erase of the stored configuration in the network element. The erase selection is write only.

uas7616LEDStatus.name: uas7616LEDStatus
uas7616LEDStatus.description: The GDC 7616 front panel LED Status. A value of 1 means on, 0 is off. byte 1 bit 7 (1.7) - not used 1.6 - not used 1.5 - loop 1 channel A (00 = No Change 01 = Green Active) 1.4 - (10 = Red Solid 11 = RedFlashing ) 1.3 - loop 1 channel B (00 = No Change 01 = Green Active) 1.2 - (10 = Red Solid 11 = RedFlashing ) 1.1 - loop 2 channel A (00 = No Change 01 = Green Active) 1.0 - (10 = Red Solid 11 = RedFlashing ) 2.7 - not used 2.6 - not used 2.5 - loop 2 channel B (00 = No Change 01 = Green Active) 2.4 - (10 = Red Solid 11 = RedFlashing ) 2.3 - loop 3 channel A (00 = No Change 01 = Green Active) 2.2 - (10 = Red Solid 11 = RedFlashing ) 2.1 - loop 3 channel B (00 = No Change 01 = Green Active) 2.0 - (10 = Red Solid 11 = RedFlashing ) 3.7 - not used 3.6 - not used 3.5 - not used 3.4 - alarm led 3.3 - test mode led 3.2 - in service 3.1 - system timing source 3.0 - management response

uas7616InterfaceType.name: uas7616InterfaceType
uas7616InterfaceType.description: Object used to configure the transmission interface type.

uas7616SysTimingGen.name: uas7616SysTimingGen
uas7616SysTimingGen.description: Selects if the unit provides system timing. none(1) - does not provide Timing Generator primary(2) - unit is primary Timing Generator for the shelf. secondary(3) - unit is secondary Timig Generator for the shelf. Only 1 unit in the shelf can the primary or secondary timing generator. All other must be none.

uas7616ResetIntervals.name: uas7616ResetIntervals
uas7616ResetIntervals.description: This variable is used to reset Loop performance intervals. When it is set to reset, the Loop performance tables are reset to zero.

uas7616SysUpTime.name: uas7616SysUpTime
uas7616SysUpTime.description: This variable is used to report the elapsed system tick time for conversion to real time at the controller and is not related to the sysUpTime referenced in MIB-II. Upon power-up of the unit, the elapsed time is cleared. The elapsed time counter rolls over upon reaching the maximum count.

uas7616SetRealTime.name: uas7616SetRealTime
uas7616SetRealTime.description: Number of seconds from midnight Dec 31, 1969.

uas7616ModuleClkSrc.name: uas7616ModuleClkSrc
uas7616ModuleClkSrc.description: This variable is used to read or set the Module Clock Source. This variable must be system when uas7616SysTimingGen is set to none. Any of the three selections when uas7616SysTimingGen is set to secondary, and internal or recovered when uas7616SysTimingGen is set to primary.

uas7616ResetMajorAlarm.name: uas7616ResetMajorAlarm
uas7616ResetMajorAlarm.description: This variable is used to reset alarm per Loop basis.

uas7616ResetMinorAlarm.name: uas7616ResetMinorAlarm
uas7616ResetMinorAlarm.description: This variable is used to reset alarm per Loop basis.

uas7616DiagnosticEntry.name: uas7616DiagnosticEntry
uas7616DiagnosticEntry.description: A listing of GDC 7616 diagnostic tests

uas7616DiagnosticIndex.name: uas7616DiagnosticIndex
uas7616DiagnosticIndex.description: A unique index for the Diagnostic Table.

uas7616DiagnosticChnlIndex.name: uas7616DiagnosticChnlIndex
uas7616DiagnosticChnlIndex.description: A unique channel index for the Channel the test will run on.

uas7616DiagnosticTest.name: uas7616DiagnosticTest
uas7616DiagnosticTest.description: Selections digitalLoopback(2), patternGenTest(3), and unitTest(4) start the associated test when written. Reading will show which (if any) test is active. Writing a stopTestwill stop the test if any was in progress.

uas7616DiagnosticResetErrorCount.name: uas7616DiagnosticResetErrorCount
uas7616DiagnosticResetErrorCount.description: This function resets the error count on a given loop and channel. Management will always read a norm(1) and can only write a reset(2).

uas7616DiagnosticResults.name: uas7616DiagnosticResults
uas7616DiagnosticResults.description: This function reads the self test results in bit errors. 2^20

uas7616AlarmConfigTable.name: uas7616AlarmConfigTable
uas7616AlarmConfigTable.description: The uas7616AlarmConfigTable contains entries that configure alarm reporting. The structure of the table is such that alarm configuration is supported on a unit and interface basis, and then on an alarm type basis within the interface. For simplicity sake alarms, be they unit or interface related, are represented in one table.

uas7616AlarmConfigEntry.name: uas7616AlarmConfigEntry
uas7616AlarmConfigEntry.description: An entry in the GDC Alarm Configuration table.

uas7616AlarmConfigIndex.name: uas7616AlarmConfigIndex
uas7616AlarmConfigIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

uas7616AlarmConfigIdentifier.name: uas7616AlarmConfigIdentifier
uas7616AlarmConfigIdentifier.description: The unique alarm identifier assigned to this alarm type. The format of this identifier is an OBJECT IDENTIFIER that has the following format: {iso(1) org(3) dod(6) internet(1) private(4) enterprises(1) gdc(498) xxx(x) alarm(z) yyy(y) where xxx(x) is the administratively assigned family object identifier (z) is the object identifier for alarms in the family defined MIB and yyy(y) is the administratively assigned alarm type identifier for this alarm.

uas7616AlarmCountWindow.name: uas7616AlarmCountWindow
uas7616AlarmCountWindow.description: This variable sets/reads the UAS, SES or ES alarm window. This window is used with the alarm threshold to determine how long the alarm should be active before reporting.

uas7616AlarmCountThreshold.name: uas7616AlarmCountThreshold
uas7616AlarmCountThreshold.description: This function sets/reads the UAS, SES or ES alarm threshold criteria. This threshold is used along with the the alarm window to determine the number of instances in a given time frame for an alarm to occur before the alarm is considered active.

uas7616Current15MinEntry.name: uas7616Current15MinEntry
uas7616Current15MinEntry.description: An entry in the 7616 Current table.

uas7616Current15MinIndex.name: uas7616Current15MinIndex
uas7616Current15MinIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface.

uas7616UnavailableTimeRegEntry.name: uas7616UnavailableTimeRegEntry
uas7616UnavailableTimeRegEntry.description: An entry in the Unavailable Time Register table.

uas7616UnavailableTimeRegIndex.name: uas7616UnavailableTimeRegIndex
uas7616UnavailableTimeRegIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface.

uas7616UnavailableTimeRegNumber.name: uas7616UnavailableTimeRegNumber
uas7616UnavailableTimeRegNumber.description: A number between 1 and 6, where the number is the number of the Unavailable Time Register.

uas7616UnavailableTimeRegStart.name: uas7616UnavailableTimeRegStart
uas7616UnavailableTimeRegStart.description: Start time of one of the Unavailable Time Registers.

uas7616UnavailableTimeRegStop.name: uas7616UnavailableTimeRegStop
uas7616UnavailableTimeRegStop.description: Stop time of one of the Unavailable Time Registers.

uas7616IntervalMaintenanceIndex.name: uas7616IntervalMaintenanceIndex
uas7616IntervalMaintenanceIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface, which in this case is a Loop interface.

uas7616NumberofValidIntervals.name: uas7616NumberofValidIntervals
uas7616NumberofValidIntervals.description: This variable is used to read the number of intervals collected. Each interval is an increment of 15 minutes.

uas7616LocalAlarmConfigTable.name: uas7616LocalAlarmConfigTable
uas7616LocalAlarmConfigTable.description: The 7616LocalAlarmConfigTable contains entries that configure alarm reporting.

uas7616LocalAlarmConfigEntry.name: uas7616LocalAlarmConfigEntry
uas7616LocalAlarmConfigEntry.description: An entry in the GDC Local Alarm Configuration table.

uas7616LocalAlarmConfigIndex.name: uas7616LocalAlarmConfigIndex
uas7616LocalAlarmConfigIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

uas7616LocalLossOfClock.name: uas7616LocalLossOfClock
uas7616LocalLossOfClock.description: Disables or enables the Loss of Clock alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

uas7616LocalUAS.name: uas7616LocalUAS
uas7616LocalUAS.description: Disables or enables the UAS alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

uas7616LocalSES.name: uas7616LocalSES
uas7616LocalSES.description: Disables or enables the SES alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

uas7616LocalES.name: uas7616LocalES
uas7616LocalES.description: Disables or enables the ES alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

uas7616LocalOutOfSync.name: uas7616LocalOutOfSync
uas7616LocalOutOfSync.description: Disables or enables the Out of Sync alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

uas7616LocalNoSealingCurrent.name: uas7616LocalNoSealingCurrent
uas7616LocalNoSealingCurrent.description: Disables or enables the No Sealing Current alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

uas7616LPMajor.name: uas7616LPMajor
uas7616LPMajor.description: Disables or enables the Major alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

uas7616LPMinor.name: uas7616LPMinor
uas7616LPMinor.description: Disables or enables the Minor alarm on the Minor buss or Minor buss.

uas7616TSAssignTable.name: uas7616TSAssignTable
uas7616TSAssignTable.description: The 7616TSAssignTable contains entries that provide a means to assign a highway and time slot of that highway to the channel of a loop.

uas7616TSAssignEntry.name: uas7616TSAssignEntry
uas7616TSAssignEntry.description: An entry in the GDC Circuit Identification table.

uas7616TSAssignIndex.name: uas7616TSAssignIndex
uas7616TSAssignIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

uas7616ChannelIndex.name: uas7616ChannelIndex
uas7616ChannelIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the channel of the interface to which this entry is applicable.

uas7616Highway.name: uas7616Highway
uas7616Highway.description: Defines the highway the channel of the loop is assigned to.

uas7616TimeSlot.name: uas7616TimeSlot
uas7616TimeSlot.description: Defines the time slot of the highway the channel of the loop is assigned to. Valid range is 1 to 31. A value of 64 indicates the channel is not assigned to a highway.

uas7616TSCircuitID.name: uas7616TSCircuitID
uas7616TSCircuitID.description: Name to identify the circuit for the channel of this loop.

uas7616mAlarmConfigTable.name: uas7616mAlarmConfigTable
uas7616mAlarmConfigTable.description: The uas7616mAlarmConfigTable contains entries that configure alarm reporting. The structure of the table is such that alarm configuration is supported on a unit and interface basis, and then on an alarm type basis within the interface. For simplicity sake alarms, be they unit or interface related, are represented in one table.

uas7616mAlarmConfigEntry.name: uas7616mAlarmConfigEntry
uas7616mAlarmConfigEntry.description: An entry in the GDC Alarm Configuration table.

uas7616mAlarmConfigIndex.name: uas7616mAlarmConfigIndex
uas7616mAlarmConfigIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

uas7616mAlarmConfigIdentifier.name: uas7616mAlarmConfigIdentifier
uas7616mAlarmConfigIdentifier.description: The unique alarm identifier assigned to this alarm type. The format of this identifier is an OBJECT IDENTIFIER that has the following format: {iso(1) org(3) dod(6) internet(1) private(4) enterprises(1) gdc(498) xxx(x) alarm(z) yyy(y) where xxx(x) is the administratively assigned family object identifier (z) is the object identifier for alarms in the family defined MIB and yyy(y) is the administratively assigned alarm type identifier for this alarm.

uas7616mAlarmCountThreshold.name: uas7616mAlarmCountThreshold
uas7616mAlarmCountThreshold.description: This function sets/reads the Major or Minor BER alarm threshold criteria.
